1
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,320
[Under the Moonlight]

2
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:29,700
[Adapted from the novel
"Jin Nang" by Shui He]

3
00:01:31,220 --> 00:01:33,020
[Episode 10]

4
00:01:33,270 --> 00:01:34,400
I'll give you two more days.

5
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:35,830
No more lies.

6
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:36,630
Alright.

7
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:52,040
Your Honor.

8
00:01:53,230 --> 00:01:54,230
Excuse me, Dr. Hua.

9
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,360
We'd like to ask you something.

10
00:01:56,830 --> 00:01:58,440
We still have some doubts
about the case.

11
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,120
We need to investigate.

12
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,480
Okay. I'll tell everything I know.

13
00:02:06,830 --> 00:02:07,510
Please.

14
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:08,440
It's okay.

15
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:09,880
We just want to know

16
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:11,440
when did you start

17
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,910
treating the Qiao family?

18
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,240
Well,

19
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,750
Shenwei and I used to be neighbors.

20
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,830
We go way back.

21
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:24,800
Then he married Qiao Ruhui,

22
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
so he moved to Qiao Mansion.

23
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,670
But he didn't forget his old friend.

24
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,600
He recommended me to be the doctor here.

25
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:33,390
I heard that Qiao Ruhui got pregnant

26
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:35,270
because of your extraordinary skills.

27
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:37,440
I can't take that credit.

28
00:02:37,830 --> 00:02:38,630
I just happened to have

29
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:39,910
a family heirloom prescription.

30
00:02:40,390 --> 00:02:41,190
Mrs. Qiao

31
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,670
really wanted to have a baby,

32
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,000
so she tried my prescription.

33
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:45,520
She really got pregnant.

34
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,030
After that,

35
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:50,270
they both trusted me a lot,

36
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:51,630
so I officially became

37
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:52,880
the doctor of the Qiao family.

38
00:02:55,630 --> 00:02:56,390
It's just too bad that

39
00:02:56,390 --> 00:02:57,830
she couldn't keep the baby alive.

40
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,190
After the miscarriage,

41
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,360
Mrs. Qiao fell seriously ill.

42
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:03,670
I had been helping her recover.

43
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,670
She had been through a lot.

44
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:07,270
She was very weak,

45
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,360
and the loss of her baby

46
00:03:08,910 --> 00:03:11,110
caused the depression
and stagnation of qi.

47
00:03:11,270 --> 00:03:13,600
She passed away.

48
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:20,160
Your prescription is so effective.

49
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:21,470
I'm sure many people

50
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,630
have come to you, right?

51
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:23,720
Yes.

52
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,240
Did that lady get pregnant

53
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:27,470
because of your prescription?

54
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:28,550
She...

55
00:03:29,270 --> 00:03:29,880
No.

56
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:31,240
She's my cousin.

57
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:33,320
Her husband's family
has been through a hard time

58
00:03:33,670 --> 00:03:34,520
and she needs money.

59
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:35,670
So,

60
00:03:35,670 --> 00:03:37,160
she came to borrow money
for an emergency.

61
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,670
Do you believe it now?

62
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,670
Qiao Ruhui did die of illness.

63
00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:46,470
Her fiery sister

64
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:47,360
accused her brother-in-law

65
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,910
of murdering for money for no reason.

66
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:50,030
That's ridiculous.

67
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:51,600
Think about it.

68
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,270
He Shenwei and his wife

69
00:03:53,270 --> 00:03:54,360
were living well

70
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,520
with no worries about life.

71
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,600
Their relationship was also good.

72
00:03:56,830 --> 00:03:58,190
Why would he take the risk to do this?

73
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,190
How would

74
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:00,320
the death of his wife benefit him?

75
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:02,240
He's just a scholar.

76
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,240
He doesn't know how to run

77
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:04,240
a liquor distillery alone.

78
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,440
Even if he got it,

79
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,750
would his life be better?

80
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,270
Don't you think

81
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:10,030
Hua Miao is a bit strange?

82
00:04:13,550 --> 00:04:14,390
Haven't you noticed

83
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:15,880
anything suspicious at all?

84
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:17,510
No.

85
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,390
In your eyes,

86
00:04:18,390 --> 00:04:19,200
everything is wrong.

87
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:20,320
Do you really think

88
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,440
Hua Miao and that woman

89
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:22,200
are cousins?

90
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:22,830
Yes.

91
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,320
Alright.

92
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:25,950
Hua Miao said

93
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:27,440
his cousin needed money

94
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:28,830
and came to borrow from him.

95
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,110
But that woman

96
00:04:30,110 --> 00:04:31,040
was wearing fine jewelry

97
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,510
and clothes made of superior material.

98
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,510
If she really needs money badly,

99
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:35,880
why did she borrow from her cousin

100
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:36,440
instead of

101
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,830
pawning her own belongings?

102
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,790
Maybe she would prefer

103
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,790
to ask people for help

104
00:04:51,790 --> 00:04:53,000
rather than suffer herself.

105
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:54,920
Even if she doesn't want to
pawn her possessions,

106
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,200
have you ever seen people borrow money

107
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:56,920
with such confidence

108
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,070
and threats?

109
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,760
It looks like she came to ask for money.

110
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,550
I'm confident.

111
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,600
Wait.

112
00:05:06,230 --> 00:05:08,000
Even if Hua Miao was lying

113
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:09,640
and that woman came to ask for money,

114
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,790
it doesn't prove anything.

115
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,320
He was saving his face

116
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:13,110
and didn't want people

117
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:14,070
to know that he owed money.

118
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,040
It shows that Hua Miao is dishonest.

119
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,640
How can you believe his words?

120
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:19,070
Fine, I'm not arguing with you.

121
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,790
You always have your reasons.

122
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,920
Even if Hua Miao was lying,

123
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,230
it has nothing to do

124
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:27,830
with He Shenwei and the Qiao family.

125
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,000
[To Ruolan]

126
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:06,110
Please wait a second.

127
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,790
You're really putting on airs.

128
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,230
Instead of sending letters to yamen,

129
00:06:10,230 --> 00:06:10,880
you asked us

130
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,920
to pick them up ourselves.

131
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:13,720
That's true.

132
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,920
These letters for me

133
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,720
are really precious

134
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:17,880
left by my sister.

135
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,440
If you were in my shoes,

136
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,440
would you just give them to somebody?

137
00:06:22,350 --> 00:06:23,200
No, no.

138
00:06:23,670 --> 00:06:24,550
It makes sense.

139
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:26,270
It's not that far

140
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,160
from yamen to here.

141
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:29,440
We can wait outside

142
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:30,320
for a while.

143
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,110
It's okay.

144
00:06:31,790 --> 00:06:32,600
Come in.

145
00:06:39,550 --> 00:06:40,720
I've organized these letters

146
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,760
in chronological order.

147
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:44,040
You can read them.

148
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,440
Okay.

149
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,760
I only show

150
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:56,320
these letters

151
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,760
to Chief Luo.

152
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,040
Besides,

153
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:00,270
I'm not used to

154
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:01,760
having other men in my room.

155
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,110
Why is it so

156
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,830
stuffy in here?

157
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,720
It smells.

158
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:16,670
I'll go for a walk.

159
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,550
Alright.

160
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:21,950
Less distractions.

161
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:44,000
You have a lot of

162
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,920
intimate conversations.

163
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:47,040
A single letter can be so long.

164
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,440
Every time I wrote to my sister,

165
00:07:49,790 --> 00:07:51,110
we always had a lot to share,

166
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:52,110
as if

167
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:53,510
she were by my side.

168
00:08:02,790 --> 00:08:04,110
Has your sister received any education?

169
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:06,790
Sure. How could she write
if she not?

170
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:08,480
I mean,

171
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:10,200
did she like reading poetry?

172
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,200
How about her writing skills?

173
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:13,640
She hasn't read a lot of poetry.

174
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:17,040
She just knew how to write, read,
and do accounting.

175
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,550
The dew on leeks,
so fragile, so fleeting.

176
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,550
It vanishes at dawn,
it will fall again in the morning.

177
00:08:21,550 --> 00:08:23,950
But once gone, my wife never returns.

178
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:27,040
You lie buried beneath the springs,
your bones dissolving.

179
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,670
I'm lodging in the world
with snow white hair.

180
00:08:30,230 --> 00:08:33,200
Unfortunately, my life is short.

181
00:08:33,590 --> 00:08:35,550
Please take care of yourself
and do not grieve.

182
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:45,110
Did you find something?

183
00:08:46,590 --> 00:08:48,030
Let me double-check with you.

184
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:49,760
These letters were wrote

185
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:50,910
before her miscarriage.

186
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:52,550
These were wrote after the miscarriage,

187
00:08:52,710 --> 00:08:53,320
right?

188
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,590
I'll write a calligraphy for you.

189
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,110
I'll definitely use the best...

190
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,910
There you are.

191
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:08,880
What do you mean?

192
00:09:09,230 --> 00:09:09,910
Of course I'm here.

193
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:10,790
It's comfortable.

194
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:13,280
Chief...

195
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,590
Chief Luo?

196
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:16,280
You...

197
00:09:16,670 --> 00:09:17,790
You're a female constable.

198
00:09:18,670 --> 00:09:19,760
I'm so impressed.

199
00:09:20,470 --> 00:09:21,440
Thank you.

200
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:22,760
Well.

201
00:09:23,110 --> 00:09:24,470
I just saw the letters

202
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:26,350
Ruhui wrote to Ruolan in Ruolan's room.

203
00:09:26,590 --> 00:09:27,960
I think you might have kept

204
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,200
some letters from Ruolan to Ruhui.

205
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,350
Can I take a look?

206
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:34,110
Chief Luo, please wait a second.

207
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,470
I'll go look for them.

208
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:43,000
He said you're pretty.

209
00:09:49,590 --> 00:09:50,840
Here you are.

210
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,520
These weren't written by Ruolan.

211
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:08,960
They're all business letters.

212
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,080
I'm very sorry.

213
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:12,520
Those letters

214
00:10:12,590 --> 00:10:14,760
were always kept by Ruhui herself.

215
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,230
I don't know where they are.

216
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:18,110
Our mansion is quite big,

217
00:10:18,470 --> 00:10:19,400
and she just passed away.

218
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:21,440
I'm still tidying the place up.

219
00:10:22,550 --> 00:10:22,960
It's okay.

220
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,760
Those are private letters.

221
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:25,840
It's normal that you don't know.

222
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:27,110
Yes.

223
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:28,710
Those letters are their secrets.

224
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,910
Even though I'm the husband,

225
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:31,550
it's not appropriate for me to know.

226
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:39,710
See.

227
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,710
You trust her,

228
00:10:40,710 --> 00:10:41,960
but she doesn't trust you.

229
00:10:45,230 --> 00:10:45,960
What?

230
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,590
You come here to watch over me?

231
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:48,960
Just to see you off.

232
00:10:54,230 --> 00:10:55,840
[Qiao Mansion]
Stop, what are you doing?

233
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,200
[Qiao Mansion]
Let me in.

234
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,470
We don't entertain guests today.

235
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,840
I want to see Mr. He.

236
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,840
I need to talk to him.

237
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:01,910
You're pregnant.

238
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:02,440
What could you

239
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,230
talk to Mr. He about?

240
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,400
Go away.

241
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:05,790
What's she doing here?

242
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:09,470
Wait.

243
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,350
[Qiao Mansion]
Who are you?

244
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:13,760
[Qiao Mansion]
What are you doing here?

245
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:19,590
What did she say to you?

246
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:21,400
She said she wanted to talk to Mr. He.

247
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:23,960
Wait.

248
00:11:24,470 --> 00:11:25,230
Hang on.

249
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,030
Who is He Shenwei to you?

250
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:29,790
Who is he to you?

251
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,000
Miss Qiao.

252
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:35,470
Qiu.

253
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:36,440
What are you doing here?

254
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,590
Miss Qiao, please calm down.

255
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,710
You've misunderstood.

256
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:44,400
She's my cousin.

257
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:45,880
Your cousin?

258
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,030
So why is she here

259
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:50,550
looking for He Shenwei?

260
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:53,760
No.

261
00:11:54,710 --> 00:11:55,880
She came here to see me.

262
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:57,590
I told her

263
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:58,350
that I was coming here

264
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,520
to examine Shenwei.

265
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:01,030
So she accidentally

266
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:02,230
said she came to see Shenwei.

267
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:06,350
You mean she came to our house
to see you?

268
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,150
She came to borrow money from me.

269
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:11,400
They are my witnesses.

270
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,000
Qiu.

271
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:21,440
You are so presumptuous.

272
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:23,110
I told you

273
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:24,400
that you had only two days.

274
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,400
But where were you?

275
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,150
If you can't do it,

276
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,550
I'll have to do it myself.

277
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,550
I'll bring the money to you today.

278
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:32,550
Just go home.

279
00:12:32,670 --> 00:12:33,760
Trying to get rid of me again?

280
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:34,550
No way.

281
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:35,320
Today,

282
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,200
the three of us...

283
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,640
I am here right now

284
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:38,710
to discuss with Shenwei.

285
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:40,590
You know I'm living on a shoestring.

286
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:42,080
I don't have extra money for you.

287
00:12:42,350 --> 00:12:43,350
I can only lend you money

288
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:44,550
if Shenwei lends it to me first.

289
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:45,840
Besides,

290
00:12:46,110 --> 00:12:46,790
I told you

291
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:47,840
to wait outside the mansion,

